(2) equip students with an understanding of the role of forensic accountants (or fraud examiners) and how a forensic accountant can assist top management in preventing, detecting and correcting frauds;
(3) strengthen students’ awareness of the significance of cyber risks in businesses and how accountants can help responding to such risks from a technical and practical perspective;
(4) strengthen students’ communication and interpersonal skills.

